===Etymology===
From {{etyl|fr|en}} {{term|facette|lang=fr}}

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ˈfæsɪt/|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# Any one of the flat [[surface]]s cut into a gem.
#: ''This '''facet''' of the diamond was masterfully cut to enhance its value.''
# One among many [[similar]] or [[related]], yet still [[distinct]] things.
#: ''The child's learning disability was only one '''facet''' of the problems contributing to his delinquency.''
# One of a [[series]] of things, such as [[step]]s in a project.
#: ''We had just about completed the research '''facet''' of the project when the order came to cancel it''.
# {{context|anatomy|lang=en}} One member of a [[compound eye]], as found in [[insect]]s and [[crustacean]]s.
# {{context|anatomy|lang=en}} A smooth circumscribed surface.
#: ''the articular '''facet''' of a bone''
# {{context|architecture|lang=en}} The narrow [[plane]] [[surface]] between [[fluting]]s of a [[column]].
# {{context|mathematics|lang=en}} A [[face]] of [[codimension]] 1 of a [[polytope]].

